					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 17th to 18th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex. </support>
								<extent>206 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>155</height>
										<width>105</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>110</height>
										<width>75</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>206 folios (+ 2 paper flyleaves at the beginning and 3 at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 6 or 8 leaves each (irregular). </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Folio missing after folio 125. </p>
									<p>Slightly stained. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="17" writtenLines="17">
									<p>Uniform layout. Visible ruling with a mastara. </p>
									<p>Initial words of each section written in larger characters, preceded with a title page (see e.g. folio 1r, 28r, etc). </p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso. </p>
									<p>The biblical verses are given with punctuation. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Square and semi-cursive Oriental scripts of the 17th to 18th century. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole">
								<p>
									<locus from="1r" to="1v"/> and <locus from="137r" to="138v"/>due to later hands.</p>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folio 205-206 belonged originally to a different manuscript. </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Mosheh Rofe ben Mosheh ha-Melamed</name>: inscribed under the titles of most of the Muḳadimat, e.g. folio 56r. </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Yosef ha-Rofe ben Mosheh ha-Rofe</name>: inscribed, folio 125v. </p>
							<p>Birth entry of Avraham, dated 5603 (1842): folio 111v . </p>
						</additions>
